        "content": "<p>Currently, a field is often denoted by <code>k</code>, but so are integer numbers or many things. I don't know how to do <code>\\mathbb{k}</code>, but I have just learned that <code>\\bbK</code> gives <code>ùïÇ</code>. Would a pull request replacing all instances of a field <code>k</code> by <code>ùïÇ</code> be welcome?</p>",
        "id": 174239172,
        "sender_full_name": "Sebastien Gouezel",
        "timestamp": 1566919249
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What about just capital <code>K</code>? That's very common in the literature.</p>",
        "id": 174239218,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1566919287
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've seen people use <code>\\bbK</code> to denote either <code>\\bbR</code> or <code>\\bbC</code>, but for general fields, I think <code>K</code> is very common.</p>",
        "id": 174239304,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1566919324
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The less ambiguity the better, I would say. And we have unicode, so let's use it!</p>",
        "id": 174239310,
        "sender_full_name": "Sebastien Gouezel",
        "timestamp": 1566919326
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, are there many other uses of <code>K</code>?</p>",
